      <highlights>At elevated altitudes a considerable avalanche danger will prevail.</highlights>
      <comment>As a consequence of new snow and wind, wind slabs formed. They must be evaluated with care and prudence. The avalanche prone locations are to be found adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain. They can be released by a single winter sport participant.</comment>
